Nice topic friend.  You thought long and hard and it shows in your post, but with a few drawbacks.  I assume this is your first and primary char?<P>Most peeps that complain have a favorite class which is their primary class of course hehehe.  I will address some issues, and this is NOT flaming, just discussion.  In preface here, I have a lvl 49 pali, 42 wizard, a 35th mage, and a host of others all in double digits.<P>Please try to refrain from comparing class x to class y.  This is Verants tactics of getting us to destroy each other.  Verant will almost always nerf another class because we say class x does this and class y cant.  Be mad at Verant, stay away from other classes for comparissons, and say what you want and why.<P>Summoned items worthless?  Im thinking of making my mage last name Seveneleven or Wallmart  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">  Im always wanted to make bandages, arrows (MAGIC mind you, able to hit any mob unlike handmade arrows that need a high skill and loads of plat), throwing daggers for rogues/monks, food and drink, bags, etc.  Maybe it is only on Rodcet Nife that people adventure without being 100% fully stocked, but I summon A LOT.<P>Water breathing stones Im always bugged for...smart peeps hunt crocs underwater in oasis (avoid giants, specs, and the crowds of peeps hunting on the shore).  Also, many quests need underwater breathing like Kedge Keep, Permafrost, Killing sharks for ro armor, etc.  Im bombarded for requests for this item, and many very fruitful hunting areas underwater  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">  Levitation?  Wiz hardly used it at all until around lvl 40.  Now, you get water breathing (wiz doesnt) and levitation (wiz needs to carry stacks of wings, you dont).<P>Mana regen:  Good topic here.  Wiz gets a spell that takes (forget now, used it 5 days and stopped) 5 to 10 min to mem, and has same recast time.  It was not even enough mana for 1 bbl.  Mages summon mana rods at will.  Also, mages pet does damage above the spells, AND keeps doing damage when you are OOM.  Wiz contribute nothing at all when oom...also you have dd's at some lvls more damage than a wiz.<P>AoE's...another good topic.  Most wiz's do not use them and plead with Verant to give us dd's instead.  AoE in general, is suicide.  6 mobs, cast AoE, and your tank fight 1 while the other 5 pummel you into goo.<P>Stun and root...good issue, until you count resists and agro.  IF wiz stun isnt resisted, 1 chance for root.  IF root sticks, it almost always breaks after our 1st nuke, so stun, root, nuke, repeat.  Earth pet always pummels time after time and keeps rooting at NO mana cost to you.<P>Damage shield (I added this) my mage has it, and mage damage shields are the best in the game bar none.  Damage shield is a aoe in a way, 12 mobs hitting your tank/pet all take damage on every hit and is unresistable.<P>Mobs dont taunt on your pet? Damage shield your pet, let it hurt mob at least 1 bbl, and use lower lvl dd's, not your best.  My mage is seldom agro'd on, mobs stick to my pet most of the time, it not I run till it re-agros pet (if Im solo'ing).  Also, remember, a wiz has no pet at all to TRY to taunt mob off  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"><P>The list continues, but suffice it to say we almost always think the grass is greener on the other side.  I play my wiz primarily for the friends I have at that lvl, and the guild needed a transport.  My mage is always been the most useful and deadlier (overall) than the wiz.  I solo mobs with mage pet and sometimes dont even cast on mob till death blow, if that <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"><P>Lastly, if you think you want the wiz powers of root, stun and (LOL) the better mana regen of a wizard, do as I did...play a wiz to the same level and see it from the other side of the fence.  You will (odds are) run screaming back to play your mage IF your guild/friends let you (we really NEED you to port us).<P>Good luck on trying to improve mage class, heck...ALL the classes are way overpowered by mobs it seems and ALL need improved, but none should be vastly superior to the others.<P>Burzug Ironfyst<BR>49th circle of training<BR>Rodcet Nife
