ve them (who needs levitate at 39? at 20 it would be useful, at 39 its just something more we can summon for newbies who dont even thank us). Also, I just outlined everything a mage can summon...that isnt much you say, and no, its not...the infravision and ultravision stones are useful only to erudite or human mages, the water breathing stone is mostly unused, the levitation ring at the level which we recieve it is not even useful anymore, bandages are good, food and drink is good to have, those pouches are useless - too small and you cant even put most items into them, and the modulating rod...well, better thought of then it actually is."<P>A-bandages <BR>-as a mage, when i solo that is, my health sometimes gets down low... and OMG there are no healers around...<BR>look in my spell book,<BR>memorize Summon Bandages...<BR>and bring my health from nothing to half full.<BR>-Warriors have forever asked me for bandages.<P>B-infravision stone <BR>-almost every human has asked me for these... <BR>-these are actually a good iteam and used for all lvls.<P>C-water breathing stone is mostly unused...<BR>-ummmmm.<BR>-These stones are more usefull in KK or any other under water zone out there then a druid casting it.<BR>( sorry all you druid out there  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/tongue.gif"> )<BR>-a Druid needs a fish scale per cast... and if OOM he can't cast it.. you Underwater breathing spells goes BYE BYE... ooooops?<BR>Wheres the mage that can summon these stones without scales... and give you them... where you can cast when YOU need it... and even if the mage is OOM it works? <BR>OOPS he/she isn't with you because you think his/her spell "Summon Water Stone" is worthless... oops.  Time to die of suffocation.<P>D-finally a ring that gives us levitation at 39,<P>-Mages can summon a ring that will Lev. whenever we right click it... it has two charges... DOESN'T take a bat wing to summon.<BR>-HOW are these useless?<P>E-everyone wants our summoned stuff!<BR>-there has not YET been a zone i haven't been asked for at least six of my summoned things... <BR>-Summoning food/water is cheaper then buying... and everyone asks for me to summon it for them.<BR>-lazy rangers and warriors don't want to BUY arrows...wheres the mage? oh HIYAS!!! can i have some arrows plz?<P>E-if you want mana regen play a chanter...<BR>-mages have the second best mana regen out of Wizzys/Chanters/Mages...<BR>-sure you loose HP when useing it... but that is what clerics are for...<BR>-casting this spell doesn't stun you, and it doesn't take ten full min.s to be fully memed and recovered... and another ten min after used.<BR>-as i said... if you want mana regen PLAY A CHANTER!!!<P><BR>Problem 3 - how do you kill monsters with a mage again?<P>A-So, the first issue with this problem is mage pets. Mage pets, every single one of them, can be easily taken out by a necro pet of same level. Throw into this equation the mage pet being buffed by the mage burnout, fire shielded by the mage fire shield, and given the best weapon the mage has: the necro pet will still win.<P>-also, AGAIN.... LIE!!!<BR>-i have dueled a necro who was my same exact lvl... no buffs on these pets at all (that means no burnout was aloud to be cast on the mage pet) and WON!<BR>-Mages pets all have their own advantages...<BR> <BR>Earth<BR>       Spell- Root<BR>       Advantages-STR & most HP<P>Air-<BR>       Spell-Invis<BR>       Advantages-(n/a)<P>Fire-<BR>       Spell-DD & buff<BR>       Advantages-fire sheild...<P>Water-<BR>       Spell-DD <BR>       Advantages-regens the fastest.<P>-we have FOUR types of pets... necros only have ONE... <BR>-what lvl pet were you useing? lvl 4???<BR>-when i played the mage (lvl 49 one) i KSed a grp on Seafuries Island in OOT with ONLY my pet... the grp was lvl 40-45s 6 of them, i didn't cast any DD's or anything...<P>Okay to summon it all up...<BR>-Mages are fine as they are.<BR>-we are in as much trouble as anyone else in every zone as anyone else...<