Havatar,<P>Woops, I did my homework, but it appears that you have not.  Bards can help others recover mana faster, however, their mana stays low.  After using Denon's Desparate Dirge, a bard is out of mana (the song drains all mana from the bard).  It will take a bard about 80 (that is eight zero, not a typo) minutes to be at full mana again.  While bard songs will help others regen mana, they do not help the bard.  Clarity helps all other mana users recover mana faster, but not bards.  Necros can twitch mana to bards (the necro loses his mana), but the bard never gets the mana.  Bards also have meditation capped at 1, which means they get no bonuses for medding other than the normal sitting increase.<P>As I said before, mages have plenty of in game methods for mana recovery, meditation, breeze, clarity, necros, at least three different bard songs, mod rods, etc.<P>Thanks for playing, please drive through.<P>Dilbis Xll &lt;Balefire Clan&gt;<BR>52nd Human Bard<BR>Tarew Marr<P>P.S.  Your make-up test will be scheduled for next Saturday morning, but the best I can do is average your grades.
