1. According to Verant, since we have an earth pet that casts root we don't need it as a spell.  While my pets have saved me dozens of times while I ran to zone, being able to cast root would've turned battles around.  A mage that wanders/sits around a mob filled area with no pet is a stupid and dead mage IMO.  We do have gate (as all casters have), but 5 seconds is too long and our pets always seem to taunt the mob off us just as we die (just like warriors).  All we need is root. The rest will get away from Verants Vision of necro/druid superiority.<P>2.  While I disagree that our summoning spells are worthless (you forgot our pets), I will agree that our summoning selection has remained stagnated while the games gear has skyrocketed.  Anyone turning down items/weapons for CR is stupid.  We save ourselves money with free food, water, and bandaids. Our summoned bags are great (if you have a good connection).  I disagree with having us make sow/clarity items.  That would make us overpowered.  I would like Verant to review the items we do summon and improve/place them in the appropriate levels, plus give us ones in line with the improved gear they have introduced to the game. I would suggest adding +5, +10, +15, +25 resist items, 1 charge per 10 levels. For those who responded to his post please do not try to "add" equipment.  Not everyone has 5000pp or belongs to a guild that has the time and manpower to ensure that all of its members characters have "uber" gear.   <P>3.  True our pets aren't equal to necros, but that is the way Verant wants it.  Verant declared druid and necro to be the only "solo" classes and has nerfed others so they could be.  They gave us monster summoning for a "cool effect", but there was no improvement on the pets themselves.  I agree that our pets fight like bards instead of warriors.  Their spells are indeed heavily resisted.  While I do not share your idea of unresistable pet spells, I do believe that Verant could fix pets by making them cast and fight at the level which they were summoned.  For those who scoff at that need to take a look at how difficult our research is.<P>I agree that our DD line should be pumped up a bit and that malise is almost worthless to cast since mob resistance doesn't seem to drop at all.  True we should be second in spell damage but that would take away from necro and druid being the top soloers.<P>Mages aren't really group friendly.  While we can support the group with an additional tank, food, water, bandaids; our spells aren't mana efficient(which requires a longer downtime) and we can be easily replaced by any other caster.<P>One thing he didn't touch on is our research.  Whomever came up with mage research needs to be slapped several times over.  While others needs 2 research items, we need 3 to 4. Plus we have to research the items at least twice, because the next level research item calls for a previous research item as an ingredient. <P>With all the nerfs going on to make necros/druids more powerful, classes like the mages aren't really viable. <P>Haquiem<BR>Wandering Mage
</FONT>
