<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Problems with the mage class:<P>Pets don't hit hard or fast enough. They are ~marginally~ better than necro pets.  And I really do mean marginally..now any of our mage pets will beat any necro pet of the same level..they are sipmly better in every single way..but they aren't good ENOUGH. At 39, my pet should hit for 44, at 44, it should hit for 50, at 51 to 54, it should hit for 60, 56 to 60, it should hit for 67.  The epic should hit for 75.  all 50+ pets should have a built in damage shield.<P>WILDFIRE: either get rid of this spell, or give us a better one.  A druid should not, ever, ever ever ever ever ever ever ever ever be able to outnuke me.  A druid isn't a nuker, yet they are given a plainly better nuke, this is intolerable, and is one of the main reasons I quit being a mage.  A druid is a damage class, and a utility/effect class, but they do it in other ways.  <P>Epic- too difficult.  Move the crown to the sixth or fifth island, make the staff 100% (or close drop) and make the cloak mage ONLY(to get rid of the competition for this item), that will bring our epic down to doable proportions.<P>Root/Stun/Snare. We need one of these, and only one. Snare would probably fit us the best, as we are supposed to be a 'solo' class, and without snare, you have very little soloing capability (shamans attest to THIS)<P>Gear- all casters across the board need gear that coincides with tank gear.  I want to have a robe that decreases my casting time, or makes my mana pool more efficient, or increases the damage of my spells, SOMETHING to allow me to keep up.<P>Resistances-have you ever landed any type of hit on Innorruuk? Ever? Ever?  The answer is probably no.<P>Until all those things are fixed, I refuse to play a magician.  All casters are broken with the advent of Kunark and Velious, but magicians are the most pathetic of the lot.  After 50, we are reduced to a support wizard, and a bad one at that.  At 55, we become a call of the hero mule.<P>What a life we get to lead.
</FONT>
