Saethan,<P>I suggest that you time it.  A bard sitting without the mana song running and sitting with the song running will both yield the same times.  The times will vary depending on your mana pool so intelligence and level do matter, but the mana song does not.  In the immortal words of Havatar Lamia:<P>"please, do the homework before taking the test."<P>This code was implemented before they were able to put timers on spells, and it was designed to limit the power of Denon's Desparate Dirge.  The song for those that don't know is a 312 point area of effect which uses 800 mana plus all of the bard's remaining mana.  This song can hardly be considered overly powerful, it should be put on a timer, and bard mana recovery should be fixed.<P>The above is not the point of the post, however.  I mostly object to someone, Disgruntled in this case, telling lies and partial truths about his class in an attempt to draw sympathy.  The fact is there are plenty of ways currently in game for a mage to recover mana faster, he just CHOOSES not to use them (my guess is that he wants to solo) and then wants to whine about it.  Please spare me the tears.<P>Dilbis Xll &lt;Balefire Clan&gt;<BR>52nd Human Bard<BR>Tarew Marr<P>P.S.  Pet classes, rogues, and anyone who can root make awesome partners for a 46+ bard.
